information.transcription:
Motor car manufacturers
Leyland Motors Ltd, incorporated as a private limited company in 1907. Name changed to Leyland Motors Ltd in 1925.
Main factory at Kingston upon Hull, with additional works at Farington and Chorley.
Produced a range of cars, including the Eight, 10/12 and 15/20 models.
Ceased car production in 1928 to focus on commercial vehicles.
